# Docker & Deployment

## Local Development
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
# Set .env DB_HOST=localhost
python app.py
```

## Docker
```bash
# Set .env DB_HOST=db
docker compose up --build
```

## Environment Variables
| Variable | Docker Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `DB_USER` | root | MySQL user |
| `DB_PASSWORD` | init1234 | MySQL password |
| `DB_HOST` | db | `db` for Docker, `localhost` for local |
| `DB_PORT` | 3306 | MySQL port |
| `DB_NAME` | sap_so_to_netsuite | Database name |
| `PORT` | 8000 | Web server port |

## Nginx Reverse Proxy
When behind Nginx, set `client_max_body_size 50M;` in server block to allow large Excel uploads.

## Container Network
- `web` service connects to `db` service via Docker internal network
- MySQL port is NOT exposed to host (uses `expose: 3306` not `ports`)
- Only the web service port is bound to host
